  • Constructor Details

    • EventIDResult

      public EventIDResult​(java.lang.String eventType, java.lang.String personID, java.lang.String city, java.lang.String country, float latitude, float longitude, int year, java.lang.String eventID, java.lang.String associatedUsername, boolean success)
      The constructor of successful instances of the EventIDResult class as reported by the EventIDService class that sets eventID, associatedUsername, personID, latitude, longitude, country, city, eventType, year, and success fields.
      Parameters:
      eventID - The eventID of the successfully found Event.
      associatedUsername - The username of the associated User taken from the successfully found Event.
      personID - The personID of the associated Person taken from the successfully found Event.
      latitude - The latitude coordinates taken from the successfully found Event.
      longitude - The longitude coordiantes taken from the successfullyh found Event.
      country - The country name taken from the successfully found Event.
      city - The city name taken from the successfully found Event.
      eventType - The event type taken from the successfully found Event.
      year - The 4-digit year taken from the successfully found Event.
      success - The boolean given by the EventIDService class. Should be true in successful instances.

    • EventIDResult

      public EventIDResult​(boolean success, java.lang.String message)
      The constructor for failed instances of the EventIDResult class that sets the success and message fields only.
      Parameters:
      success - The boolean indicating the result of the EventIDService class. Should be false in failed instances.
      message - The message containing the specific error or details of the failed request.
